article.headline: Northwestern St. 34, Stephen F.Austin 24
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Dudley Guice caught 11 passes for 190 yards and a touchdown as Northwestern State beat Stephen F. Austin 34-24 on Saturday night. John Hundley was 29-of-44 passing for 294 yards to lead the Demons (7-5, 4-3 Southland). Hundley ran 12 times for another 42 yards and a score. Jeremy Moses hit 22 of 44 passes for 241 yards and a touchdown to lead Stephen F. Austin, but threw four interceptions. Cornel Tarrant ran 10 times for 90 yards and a score for the Lumberjacks (4-8, 2-5). Dominque Edison caught a touchdown pass for Stephen F. Austin, establishing a new conference TD reception record with 28.
